Subject: Re: [T2] sockets: regular versus impact

On Monday, May 30, 2005, at 07:05PM, Jack Dinan <jdinan(-at-)cox.net> wrote:

>I broke my 19mm socket trying to coax lug bolts off the wheels of a 
>newly purchased vehicle.
>I would like to buy just this individual socket. My favorite catalog 
>has sections for regular sockets and other sections for impact 
>sockets.
>What is the difference?

The basic difference is that the finish on an impact socket won't chip like chrome will on a regular socket. Not a factor for a ratchet but it becomes one when you drive it with an air powered impact gun.

